##A plague victim from Wuhan, China: 33 Days of isolation

XISUMJC

MJC Professional Practice Communication Platform for Xi'an International Studies University. A true record of the living conditions of foreigners in Shaanxi and Shaanxi people abroad. With vivid and vivid stories, the cultural separation, collision and communication between self and other under the background of globalization are observed. The state of the other, the state of the visitor.

In the early hours of January 23rd, on the eve of New Year's Eve, the city of Wuhan was closed to traffic. Had it not been for the outbreak, Dindin would have been in Henan by now, with his sister, who had come from Dangyang.

It was her long-planned trip. Because of his busy work and lack of holidays, Dindin has traditionally spent the past few years traveling during the Spring Festival.

On the 20th, Dindin received a message from a former colleague, a nurse at Concorde Hospital, informing her that the outbreak was serious and that it was risky to travel. After much deliberation, she and her sister reached an agreement, pressing the "cancel now" button on their airline and hotel reservations.

On Feb. 25, Dindin was interviewed online, her 33rd day in isolation at home since Jan. 23.

The night before last

On January 21,2020, two days before the Wuhan government announced it was shutting down the city, Dindin went to work as usual. As usual with work, there is the morning rush hour in Wuhan subway. "there were still many passengers, only a small number of them wearing masks. Because there was an outbreak on the Internet, but it wasn't officially announced, so most people, like me, just let it go. On January 23rd, twenty-nine of the Lunar New Year's days, Wuhan officially closed the city.

The bustling Wuhan Pedestrian Street (Chuhehan Street)
@ Lin Chen hearing

Dindin takes his annual vacation every year, and this year is no exception. She and her sister had planned this trip for a long time. Buy A ticket, book a hotel, do strategy, all the preparations are ready. Had it not been for the outbreak, Dindin would have met his sister, who had come from Dangyang, and taken a bus to Henan. On the eve of her trip, a friend who works at Concorde Hospital told her that the outbreak seemed "a bit serious, " but that didn't stop her from traveling at the time. "Two or three days before the city was closed, my friend again sent me a message telling me not to go out. She had already returned all the tickets she had bought for Mount Lu. She said the situation was 'very serious' and that going out would be 'very risky' . "Dindin became worried and told her sister about the situation. They decided to cancel the trip and call it a year.

"when the news first started reporting the outbreak at the South China Seafood Market, my colleagues told me that they were going to the drugstore to buy some face masks for me. They asked me if I wanted them. I laughed and said, 'iron woman doesn't need face masks. ' ".

As this was being overwhelmed by the raging epidemic, Dindin became wary of the severity of the situation. "I didn't wear a mask until the city was shut down. Every morning when going to work, the subway, the bus is crowded with people, wearing masks are not many, including me, the street is only a part of the people wear. But thankfully, it's not infected. I'm a very slow person when it comes to the importance of the epidemic. "later, when he told his family about the experience, Dindin thought he was so lucky.
Customers line up at the supermarket entrance to take their temperature
@ Lin Chen hearing

"As a native of Wuhan, I feel that the city really took action much later than other areas in terms of epidemic prevention measures. " according to Dindin's sister in Dangyang, a county-level city in Yichang, "the epidemic prevention measures there were carried out three or four days earlier than in Wuhan, " and she later saw on the Internet how Henan was responding to the epidemic, still, Dindin said, Wuhan has been far less focused on the disease than it has been in the past.

Quarantined

After the city was shut down, people were barred from all parts of Wuhan, including the neighborhood where Dindin lived. Unprepared, the sudden restrictions disrupted the Dindin family's rhythm of life. "I don't remember exactly when the block was closed down. It was accessible at the beginning, because we bought a week's worth of stuff at a time, so the family didn't go out much. Later, the community issued a form, the above allowed each family three days to send out a person to purchase supplies, I also quickly went to pick up the table, go out and buy a need. "

That purchase scared Dindin. "The first time I went to the shopping center across the street, there was a long line in front of me. Everyone was self-conscious and the distance between people was long. Supermarket staff kept coming out and shouting to keep a safe distance. They also took their temperature before entering the supermarket. But after shopping and waiting in line to be weighed, people were huddled together. It was a scene where my face was on someone's back, and their face was on my back, and the whole team was like a snake. I'm scared. "
People in Wuchang District shop at supermarkets
@ Lin Chen hearing

Since then, Dindin, a former nurse, has become alarmed that her daily routine needs to be put on "DEFCON 1. ". "When I get home, I'm going to sterilize everything at the door, and then I'm going to spray myself with alcohol, including the soles of my shoes, which I would never put in my house, which makes me feel like I'm back in the operating room, all articles must be sterilized to the strictest standard. "

In the early days of the quarantine, the vast city of Wuhan could not buy a bottle of alcohol, let alone a mask. "Once commissioned the community to buy alcohol, the quality was in doubt. A 500 ML bottle of alcohol for 25 yuan, almost as much as two bottles of mineral water, surprisingly cheap, but when I opened it was clearly a very heavy smell of high white wine... very helpless, but also can only be used. "although it has been a month, these anti-epidemic necessities are still in short supply. Dindin told us that she now has only six face masks left in her house, so she saves them every time. She doesn't go out wearing a mask just to buy something, she has to make a shopping list, go out a time will need to buy things all at once, try to put a mask to maximum effect.
A sweaty old lady with a plastic bag over her head in a supermarket
@ Lin Chen hearing

The opportunity to go out is not much, but the family always has to live, some food is still very scarce, she and her mother tried to buy goods through various channels. Because the distribution quota is scarce, just began to grab three or four times on the fresh horse did not grab. "As crazy as singles' Day. "Dindin said, laughing. "Then someone in the owner's group shared how to do it, and did it his way before they got it. I bought about 800 yuan worth of food that time. I can eat it till the middle of March at least. "

The order was placed, and the waiting time for the rider to deliver the goods was agonizing, with delays a common occurrence. "I had to wait downstairs for almost four hours to get my stuff because I had two orders and had to go home and change my mask again. "
Volunteers hand out vegetables outside the community
Graph source network

We only have enough food for one day. "There are groups in the community that buy vegetables and things like that, but some people in the owners' group complain that the vegetables they buy are bad and the photos don't look good. Finally, I had no choice but to ask volunteers to buy some things. About 200 yuan of vegetables, short of two catties not to say, the original two catties of things I went home weighing only a little more than a catty; the price is more than twice as expensive as usual. What can be done? In Times like these, it's nice to have something to eat. "said Dindin, with a Helpless Sigh.

"Not only is it impossible to buy food, but even if you are lucky enough to get it, it is not convenient to go out and get it yourself. Volunteers with permits in Dindin's neighborhood helped the owners pick up the food, but instead of delivering it to their front door, they put it in a fixed place. Self-pick point in the community across the road, Walk to take about 10 minutes, more than double the price of food than usual, each order also have to pay an extra 30 yuan for the cost of the purchase.
Who was delivering food during the outbreak
@ Lin Chen hearing

Dindin loved fish and talked about it every day at home for a while. But in times of disease, that is a luxury. "I had a dream one night that I would catch fish with my colleagues, and now I can't believe it. "

Fire in the heart

On January 22, Dindin posted a message on her facebook page, saying, "I'd like to volunteer, " complete with a picture of her nurse's license.
DINDIN's instagram photo

At the height of the outbreak in Wuhan, watching the daily headlines Rolling in the news media, Dindin recalled the days five years ago when he was shuttling from hospital to hospital. At that time she was an ordinary nurse in a hospital in Wuhan.

She had been away from her job for many years, but she was aware of how scarce health care resources were at this time. And so, the idea of volunteering came to me. I reached out to my best friend at the hospital and told her about the idea of volunteering. She told me that there was an opportunity to volunteer at the Red Cross, and her main job was to answer the phone and contact donors and stuff like that. But because the Red Cross was far away from home, traffic was stopped, the weather was unpredictable and she did not own a car, commuting was a big problem, which became her biggest concern.

Dindin was going to ask her mother for advice. At first she was very supportive. "Do I need old people? "? She wants to go, too. I was secretly glad that my mother understood me. "later, when she learned from the television news that the outbreak was getting worse, especially when she saw the scenes of separation... in the end, when Dindin showed her the recruitment notice, her attitude changed 180 degrees, "It's going to be a long time, not a day or two, and the girls will be tired. "She could not bear her mother's insinuations. She was the only one left in the house. What would she do if something happened to her? With more work to do at the company, Dindin eventually gave up the opportunity to volunteer.

Not Helpful, but she was concerned about her former colleagues at the hospital as she watched the news coverage of new cases go up. Although they are not in the front line, but the increasingly severe epidemic or their work to add a lot of difficulties. "when the traffic ban first started, they didn't have a pass or anything like that, so they had to stay in a nearby hotel or live with a co-worker who rented a room. You need to wear protective clothing to work, but you can hardly drink water at work, as it takes a long time to pull it off once, and there is a risk of letting bacteria in. "
Zhongnan Hospital of Wuhan University
@ Lin Chen hearing

A close friend suspected the virus and took a nucleic acid test, Dindin said. The results were good, but it would take a second test to be sure. In order to get a good result, her friend's mother even took the child's Eight Characters to ask the Fortune Teller, which is a kind of spiritual sustenance. Actually, when he said that, I thought it was funny. People in the helpless to the extreme, may feel that only God can bless themselves. "

Postscript

The last batch of 49 patients emerged from the Wembley Arena at 3:30 pm on March 10, according to the latest news from Wuhan. After 35 days of operation, Wuhan's First Shelter Hospital was officially closed. So far, all 14 shelter hospitals in Wuhan have closed their cabins.

Dindin said masks can now be ordered in Wuhan, alcohol is available, fresh supplies are available, there is no need to snap up drastic, 38 days in Taobao orders of express delivery has been received. Of course, she can finally eat the fish she wants.

Spring is here, and the Cherry blossoms are about to bloom in Wuhan.
Cherry blossoms in full bloom in Wuhan
Graph source network

We'll meet again when the cherry blossoms are in full bloom.
